Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Four wanted men were arrested at a shopping centre in Sunninghill, Sandton, police said on Thursday.&nbsp;They were wanted for serious crimes including armed robbery, robbery and murder, Captain Kay Makhubele said.Makhubele said the men were found in possession of two unlicenced R5's, one pistol, a radio, two reflectors and one jamming device.&nbsp;"We also found two suspected stolen vehicles, a BMW and a Toyota Corolla," Makhubele said.They were arrested late on Thursday afternoon and were expected to appear in the Randburg Magistrate's Court soon.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.